<subSubSection pageId="113" pageNumber="114" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="113.[151,1437,1003,1463]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
Priestfish or 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[726,816,1256,1282]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Skilfish</emphasis>
. To 
<quantity box="[871,956,1256,1283]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.88" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="cm" value="188.0">188 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[974,1035,1256,1283]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8796" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="in" value="74.0">74 in</quantity>
) TL (
<bibRefCitation author="Zolotov" box="[1103,1331,1256,1282]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Zolotov" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" pagination="251 - 265" refId="ref335189" refString="Zolotov, O. G., Spirin, I. Yu. &amp; Zudina, S. M. (2014) New data on the range, biology, and abundance of skilfish Erilepis zonifer (Anoplopomatidae). Journal of Ichthyology, 54, 251 - 265. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / s 0032945214020131" type="journal article" year="2014">
Zolotov 
<emphasis box="[1203,1261,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). Sagami Bay, Pacific coast of central Honshu, 
<collectingCountry box="[621,685,1293,1319]" name="Japan" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mecklenburg, C. W." box="[699,917,1292,1318]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" refId="ref300506" refString="Mecklenburg, C. W. (2003) Family Anoplopomatidae Jordan &amp; Gilbert 1883 - sablefishes. California Academy of Sciences, Annotated Checklists of Fishes, No. 2." type="book" year="2003">Mecklenburg 2003</bibRefCitation>
), to south of Commander–Aleutian chain, and southern Gulf of Alaska (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[634,689,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2002), to Monterey Bay, central California (
<bibRefCitation author="Eschmeyer and Herald" firstAuthor="Eschmeyer" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" refId="ref277744" refString="Eschmeyer, W. N. &amp; Herald, E. S. (1983) A Field Guide to Pacific Coast Fishes of North America from the Gulf of Alaska to Baja California. Houghton Mifflin, Boston." type="book" year="1983">Eschmeyer and Herald 1983</bibRefCitation>
). Depth: juveniles and young adults to about 
<quantity box="[760,841,1364,1391]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="cm" value="110.0">110 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[856,915,1364,1391]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0922" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="in" value="43.0">43 in</quantity>
) TL collected near surface, sometimes close to shore (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[432,489,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2002); adults close to bottom; depth: 
<quantity box="[920,1069,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.235" metricValueMax="10.47" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="m" value="623.5" valueMax="1047.0" valueMin="200.0">200–1,047 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1084,1234,1400,1427]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.239256" metricValueMax="10.479023999999999" metricValueMin="1.999488" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="ft" value="2047.0" valueMax="3438.0" valueMin="656.0">656–3,438 ft</quantity>
), usually far from shore (min.: Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[496,552,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2002; max.: 
<bibRefCitation author="Zolotov" box="[700,919,1436,1462]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Zolotov" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" pagination="251 - 265" refId="ref335189" refString="Zolotov, O. G., Spirin, I. Yu. &amp; Zudina, S. M. (2014) New data on the range, biology, and abundance of skilfish Erilepis zonifer (Anoplopomatidae). Journal of Ichthyology, 54, 251 - 265. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / s 0032945214020131" type="journal article" year="2014">
Zolotov 
<emphasis box="[795,852,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
).
